=Description=

"If you live in a city experiencing rapid urbanization, you know it's hard to agree on how to inclusively utilize important urban goods. What practical tools and governance forms can residents and policymakers rely on to come to a satisfactory agreement? We’re joined by Sheila Foster, Professor of Law and Public Policy at Georgetown University, to talk about the Co-Cities project that investigates new forms of collaborative city-making."

